#: manafirewall/helpinfo.py:36
msgid ""
"Permanent mode allows you to configure things that are not immediately "
"active. If you also want changes to be active in the runtime environment, "
"either add them there as well or reload firewalld."
msgstr ""

#: manafirewall/helpinfo.py:37
msgid ""
"Runtime mode allows you to configure things at runtime. Things changed at "
"runtime will not persist after the next start up or firewalld reload; if you "
"want them to persist, you need to add those changes in permanent mode as "
"well."
msgstr ""

#: manafirewall/helpinfo.py:38
msgid ""
"A zone is a set of services that can be applied to a binding. A collection "
"of zones is predefined for different levels of trust. If you select the "
"\"Permanent\" configuration, you can also add, edit or delete your own zone "
"and define which services will be allowed in your zone. "
msgstr ""
"Een zone is een set diensten die toegepast kan worden op een binding. Een "
"collectie zones is reeds gedefinieerd voor verschillende vertrouwensniveaus. "
"Als u de \"Permanente\" configuratie kiest, kunt u uw eigen zone toevoegen, "
"bewerken of verwijderen en instellen welke diensten in uw zone toegestaan "
"zijn."

#: manafirewall/helpinfo.py:39
msgid ""
"For a zone, available fields are name, version, short (a more descriptive "
"name), and description. A check box allows you to activate the default "
"target or to select the default behaviour for packets that don't match any "
"rule. Targets are DROP, REJECT or ACCEPT. "
msgstr ""

#: manafirewall/helpinfo.py:40
msgid ""
"Predefined zones are: block - dmz - drop - external - home - internal - "
"public - trusted - work"
msgstr ""

#: manafirewall/helpinfo.py:41
msgid ""
"After selecting \"Zones\" as the View and one of the Zones, you can "
"configure the selected zone. There are some parameters for each zone:"
msgstr ""

#: manafirewall/helpinfo.py:42
msgid ""
"<ul><li><b>Services</b>: when selected in the \"Configure\" option, you see "
"a list of predefined services. According to the zone, some services are "
"already selected. If you tick or untick a checkbox for a service, the "
"corresponding rules will be applied to allow or deny that service on "
"interfaces using the zone. In permanent mode, the configuration is "
"registered directly but not applied immediately; it will be applied after a "
"firewalld reload.</li>"
msgstr ""

#: manafirewall/helpinfo.py:43
msgid ""
"<li><b>Ports</b>: this option allows you to define a rule using the \"Add\" "
"button, specifying a port number or range and a protocol selected from the "
"list tcp, udp, sctp and dccp. The list view displays the already defined "
"rules. A range is specified with a hyphen between two numbers, for example "
"80-88. The effect is that those ports will be open.</li>"
msgstr ""

#: manafirewall/helpinfo.py:44
msgid ""
"<li><b>Protocols</b>: Here, you can add a protocol from a list of protocols "
"supported by firewalld, or add a custom one by name.</li>"
msgstr ""

#: manafirewall/helpinfo.py:45
msgid ""
"<li><b>Source Ports</b>: this option allows you to define a rule using the "
"\"Add\" button, specifying a source port number or range and a protocol "
"selected from the list tcp, udp, sctp and dccp. The list view displays the "
"already defined rules.</li>"
msgstr ""

#: manafirewall/helpinfo.py:46
msgid ""
"<li><b>Masquerading</b>: this option allows you to enable or disable "
"masquerading for the zone (IPv4 only).</li>"
msgstr ""

#: manafirewall/helpinfo.py:47
msgid ""
"<li><b>Port Forwarding</b>: port forwarding is an application of network "
"address translation (NAT) that redirects a communication request from one "
"address and port number combination to another while the packets are "
"traversing the firewall (IPv4 only). Adding a rule requires specifying a "
"port or port range for incoming requests and its protocol (source), and "
"either a port or range for the destination for local forwarding, or an "
"address and optional port or range if the destination address changes.</li>"
msgstr ""

#: manafirewall/helpinfo.py:48
msgid "<li><b>ICMP Filter</b>: not yet implemented</li>"
msgstr "<li><b>ICMP Filter</b>: nog niet geïmplementeerd</li>"

#: manafirewall/helpinfo.py:49
msgid "<li><b>Rich Rules</b>: not yet implemented</li>"
msgstr "<li><b>Rich Rules</b>: nog niet geïmplementeerd</li>"

#: manafirewall/helpinfo.py:50
msgid "<li><b>Interfaces</b>: not yet implemented</li>"
msgstr "<li><b>Interfaces</b>: nog niet geïmplementeerd</li>"

#: manafirewall/helpinfo.py:51
msgid "<li><b>Sources</b>: not yet implemented</li></ul>"
msgstr "<li><b>Sources</b>: nog niet geïmplementeerd</li></ul>"

#: manafirewall/helpinfo.py:53
msgid ""
"A service is a collection of rules that are applied together in relation to "
"an application. This concept helps to apply what is needed for an "
"application by just ticking a checkbox. A lot of services are already "
"defined, but you can add your own for an application that is not provided."
msgstr ""

#: manafirewall/helpinfo.py:54
msgid ""
"In the \"Services\" view, the \"Configure\" button next to the combobox "
"allows you to choose a service. Selecting one updates the table with a list "
"of Port-Protocol pairs."
msgstr ""

#: manafirewall/helpinfo.py:55
msgid "For each service, you can define:"
msgstr "Voor elke dienst kunt u definiëren:"

#: manafirewall/helpinfo.py:56
msgid ""
"<ul><li><b>Ports</b>: when selected, the list view contains the ports "
"already defined. Each port is defined by a number or a range, and a protocol."
"</li>"
msgstr ""
"<ul><li><b>Poorten</b>: indien geselecteerd, laat de lijstweergave de reeds "
"gedefinieerde poorten zien. Elke poort is gedefinieerd door een getal of "
"getallenreeks en een protocol.</li>"

#: manafirewall/helpinfo.py:57
msgid "<li><b>Protocols</b>: not yet implemented</li>"
msgstr "<li><b>Protocollen</b>: nog niet geïmplementeerd</li>"

#: manafirewall/helpinfo.py:58
msgid "<li><b>Source Ports</b>: not yet implemented</li>"
msgstr "<li><b>Bronpoorten</b>: nog niet geïmplementeerd</li>"

#: manafirewall/helpinfo.py:59
msgid "<li><b>Modules</b>: not yet implemented</li>"
msgstr "<li><b>Modules</b>: nog niet geïmplementeerd</li>"

#: manafirewall/helpinfo.py:60
msgid "<li><b>Destination</b>: not yet implemented</li></ul>"
msgstr "<li><b>Bestemming</b>: nog niet geïmplementeerd</li></ul>"

#: manafirewall/helpinfo.py:64
msgid ""
"ManaFirewall is a graphical configuration tool for firewall features "
"provided by firewalld."
msgstr ""
"ManaFirewall is grafische configuratietool voor firewallfuncties van "
"firewalld."

#: manafirewall/helpinfo.py:65
msgid ""
"firewalld provides a dynamically managed firewall with support for network/"
"firewall “zones” to assign a level of trust to a network and its associated "
"connections, interfaces or sources."
msgstr ""
"firewalld voorziet in een dynamisch beheerde firewall met ondersteuning voor "
"network/firewall-“zones” om een vertrouwensniveau toe te kennen aan een "
"netwerk en de daamee samenhangende verbindingen, interfaces of bronnen."

#: manafirewall/helpinfo.py:66
msgid ""
"It has support for IPv4, IPv6, Ethernet bridges and also for IPSet firewall "
"settings. There is a separation of the runtime and permanent configuration "
"options."
msgstr ""
"Het ondersteunt IPv4, IPv6, Ethernet-bridges en ook IPSet- "
"firewallinstellingen. De runtime en permanente configuratie-opties zijn "
"gescheiden."

#: manafirewall/helpinfo.py:67
msgid ""
"ManaFirewall is part of manatools and it is based on manatools.aui so that "
"it can work using Qt (PySide6), GTK 4, or ncurses, i.e. both graphical and "
"textual user interfaces."
msgstr ""

#: manafirewall/helpinfo.py:68
msgid ""
"On the left there is the overview of the active bindings. These are the "
"zones, that have a connection, interface or source bound or added to it. "
"Here it is possible to easily change the zone of these bindings."
msgstr ""

#: manafirewall/helpinfo.py:69
msgid ""
"On the right there are comboboxes to select what to look or configure such "
"as zones, services etc."
msgstr ""
"Rechts zijn de comboboxes om te selecteren wat te zoeken of configureren, "
"zoals zones, diensten enz."

